    "details": {
      "blurb": "Umbral dragon; SPIRIT ANCHOR (B23)",
      "languages": {
        "details": "",
        "value": [
          "common",
          "draconic",
          "shadowtongue"
        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 15
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> umbral dragon of the old kennels (B23), lured decades ago by legends of Kazavon's treasury. He destroyed one of Mithrodar's anchors — the undead general <strong>Gorstav</strong> — to loot in peace, and the chained spirit snared <em>him</em> as the replacement. Centuries of failed escapes have left him bored, listless, dangerous. <strong>On noticing PCs he attacks for the thrill — but his true desire is freedom.</strong> Told the PCs mean to release the anchors, he goes utterly still and silent: his only legal way to signal they're on the right track. <strong>Morale:</strong> he knows dying here binds his soul to Scarwall forever — below ~110 HP he turns craven, flees to his lair to hide and heal, and if cornered begs for mercy and offers his hoard (B24) as bribe; if his anchor-bond is broken mid-fight he breaks off, screeches in victory, and flees the region abandoning everything. He fights to kill only if the PCs commit to killing him. <strong>Freed (not slain):</strong> he perches on a tor over the tarn and gratefully plays hint-dispenser on Scarwall's denizens, layout, and perils — though he knows nothing of the donjon or Star Tower and little of the guest wing (asked about Serithtial, he guesses one of the former).</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
        "authors": "",
        "license": "OGL",
        "remaster": true
      }
